tip.text: Been here twice. Great place to stay, a little bit far fro the city. Big and comfortable room. Their dinner concept is good and delicious. Love this place.
Enak buat nyantai. But there is nothing in here.
Try jumping from this bridge. Its fun.
Its so cheap to get here, only cost around 40.000 rupiah to get to this beautiful island. But don't go here in high season, Its so dirty and so crowded by a lot of people.
New mall, it's still takes times to fully operated. But its great place to hang out. Especially I love their outdoor view concept. The wind from the sea feels so refreshing.

Worth to try, The drink taste good.
The food taste good, big portion. Take their package for cheaper price.

tip.text: They have lots variation of tea and try their macarons, its delicious.

location.address: #B2-89/89A, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

tip.text: Great place to have some fun. its open 24 hours, but please be careful don't get addicted to it. No photo allowed in here. No short pants, no sandal, and need passport to get in. Free drink inside.
Lots of foods there, I got confuse to chose one because all looks so delicious. Char kwetiau and fried oyster is so delicious.
Its my favorite mall in Singapore. love the food court, and I especially like their roof top. Well design.
Good food, taste great.
Go there at night, The light is so beautiful.
Take a cable car when sun set. You'll get a sunset view and night view as well. You'll see a magnificent view. One of my most memorable sunset view.
A glass of wine and a piece of cake for dessert while waiting for sunset at Mount Fiber Singapore. What a beautiful day, one of my most memorable day.

formattedAddress: The Jewel Box (109 Mount Faber Rd.)

tip.text: Love every part of it when walking from mount fiber to Henderson waves bridge.
Waiting so that we can ride the cable car while seeing sunset. Its worth the wait.
Beautiful bridge in the middle of nowhere. its so hot in the afternoon. better go there at the evening.

location.crossStreet: Connecting Telok Blangah Hill Park & Mt Faber Park
formattedAddress: Henderson Rd (Connecting Telok Blangah Hill Park & Mt Faber Park)

tip.text: Don't wait there for check in and doing nothing, Just told them to prepare your room at 4 pm, so that you just need to take the key at that time. And while waiting, go seeing sea aquarium. Great pool.
Have some night jungle adventure with a lot of animals here. Long queue.
What is a perfect food in the hot weather? It's Ice cream. And that is exactly what we do, eating Ice cream in the afternoon while waiting for night safari.

formattedAddress: Singapore Zoo Entrance (80 Mandai Lake Road)

tip.text: A good place to cool our self after a hot day at River Safari. just eat their dimsum and drink some cup of tea.

venue.name: River Safari Tea House 河川茶居

tip.text: I went there just to see one animal. PANDA. Its so cute and you won't be bored even if you stare him for an hour.
Big dome filled with flower everywhere, and the best part is the dome is smelled with flower scent. love it so much. the flower is beautiful.
You have to eat here at least once if you are near the china town. but beware for a long queue when lunch time. taste soooo good and cheap as well.

formattedAddress: #02-126, Chinatown Complex Market & Food Centre (335 Smith St)

venue.name: Hong Kong Soya Sauce Chicken Rice & Noodle

tip.text: Take a photo here with the Merlion statue and marina bay sands hotel as the background. My most favorite photo view in Singapore. Better view at night.
You got to try their Ice cream, taste so good. Candy lover and chocolate lover will love this shop.
What can I say, just go there and see it yourself. Love it, Love it, Love it.
It's used to be a very beautiful beach, but its so dirty when I was there. And because I more like quiet beach, now I prefer Sanur beach at the east Bali.
Been here few years ago. Booked a Family room (1 king size bed + 3 bunk bed). Quiet pricy but worth to stay there. Its near the mall and Kuta beach at the back of the hotel.
Long queue, especially at lunch or dinner time. But its worth to wait there. The cafe is so cozy, comfortable, great for hang out. the food and drink is sooo good. I love this place.
